title: LOKI and DOCTOR STRANGE Each Saw the Multiverse | Full VISION Frame by Frame BREAKDOWN
author: ScreenCrush
comment: This Screencrush guy is pulling far ahead from all the other comic book YouTube channels. More than covering Easter eggs and spoilers, he has really interesting, very perceptive story analysis.
Damn I never would have realised that that epic opening in Loki episode 6 was all Loki's vision at the end of episode 5. Thanks Dr. Screencrush
This guy is absolutely incredible, I would never be able to figure out something like this. Always good to have someone like you to tell us about this awesome stuff.

At like 9:45 he talks about the nightmare dimension. In episode 1? of Loki, Loki says, “This place is a nightmare.” (Referring to the TVA) And Mobius says, “No. that’s a different division, now that place I’ll help you burn down.” Could Mobius be talking about the actual nightmare dimension?
Fun fact: the pineal gland, located in the brain, actually has a cornea similar to the eyeballs. Literally the "third eye".
